You turn the first card.

The crew watches. Scout is leaning so far over the counter he's practically lying on it. Mal stands behind him, notebook closed, arms crossed — the posture of someone who has cataloged every book in this store and is about to find out the store has been cataloging them back. Delphi is still, her hand on the counter, palm flat on the wood.

**{session.p1_card.get_display_name()}.**

