# ---------- SIX OF CUPS ----------

:: TheKind.Session3.P1_SixCups

@if session.p1_card.reversed:
    The Six of Cups, inverted. The children in the garden — the nostalgia card, the memory card, the card of gifts given freely — are upside down. The cups spill. The flowers wilt. What was sweet turns saccharine, what was memory turns to trap.

    The turntable behind the counter hums a melody. Faint. Something old — a few notes, a fragment, the ghost of a song the store once played for someone who needed it. Then it fades. The store reaching for a memory and finding it bittersweet.
@else:
    Six of Cups. Two children in a garden, one offering flowers to the other. Nostalgia, gifts freely given, the sweetness of memory when memory is kind. The card of a place that remembers everything and gives without counting.

    The turntable hums. A melody nobody recognizes but everyone feels — a few warm notes, like a lullaby heard through a wall. The store singing to itself. The pressed tin ceiling catches the lamplight and throws old, golden patterns on the hardwood — the shadows of a building remembering its own history.
@endif

"Position one. What you've been holding."

Scout reaches for the card, stops himself. "Sorry. Force of habit."

