    + ["The Hermit holds a lantern. You've been lighting the way for everyone else. Who lights the way for you?"] -> TheKind.Session3.P2_Hermit_Lantern
    + ["You've kept your own counsel because nobody spoke your language. But we're learning."] -> TheKind.Session3.P2_Hermit_Language
    + ["Isolation. Withdrawal. Maybe the store just needs some alone time."] -> TheKind.Session3.P2_Hermit_Dismiss
@endif

:: TheKind.Session3.P2_Hermit_Alone
"You've been alone with this," you say. "However long you've been here — years, decades, longer — you've had something to say and nobody asked. Not because they didn't care. Because they didn't know you were *talking.*"

The lights dim to candlelight warmth. The storm outside goes quiet for three seconds — three full seconds of absolute silence, the rain stopping, the wind stopping, everything stopping, as if the weather itself is holding its breath to let the store's silence become audible.

Then the rain returns. But softer. Gentler. Like it understood.

Delphi's eyes are bright. Not crying — Delphi doesn't cry, or if she does, not where people can see. But bright.

"She's been saying it the whole time," Delphi says. "The turntable starting on its own. The records that surface at the right moment. The deep shelves opening when someone needs them. She's been *talking.* We just thought it was ambiance."

