:: TheKind.Session3.Transition_P2_P3
~ session.store_expressiveness += 3

Two cards on the counter. What she's been holding. What she hasn't said. The store has been read more in the last twenty minutes than in its entire existence and you can *feel* the difference — the building is breathing differently, humming on a different frequency, alive in a way that goes beyond warm-and-cozy into something more specific. Something with intention.

The storm outside has settled into a steady downpour. No more theatrical lightning. The thunder has said what it needed to say. Now it's just rain — heavy, constant, the sound of the sky matching the store's energy: persistent, insistent, unapologetic.

@if session.quality_score >= 5:
    The store is radiant. Not a metaphor — actually, physically radiant. The pressed tin ceiling is throwing patterns of light that don't correspond to any lamp in the building. The bead curtain is swaying in a rhythm that matches your pulse. The temperature is exactly perfect — not warm, not cool, the temperature of being held. The Kind is fully present, fully expressed, fully *here* in a way it has never been while you've worked here.

    "She trusts you," Delphi says. Almost reverently.

    "She trusts *us,*" Scout corrects. For once, he's right. This isn't about the reader. This is about the crew.
@elif session.quality_score >= 2:
    The store is warm. Present. Listening. Cautiously open — the way a person opens who isn't sure yet if this conversation is going to go the way they want. The lamp sways gently. The deep shelves hum. Not fully expressed, but getting there.

    Delphi: "One more card. Make it count."
@else:
    The store is holding steady. Neither open nor closed. Waiting. The kind of patience that is actually a warning — the patience of someone who will ask one more time and then stop asking.

    Delphi: "Last card. She's still here. Don't waste it."
@endif

"Last card," you say. To the crew. To the store. To the pressed tin ceiling and the humming deep shelves and the rain on the roof. "What you want for yourself."

This is the one that matters. This is the question the store cleared the thunder for.

+ [Turn the third card] -> TheKind.Session3.Position3

