# ---------- THE WORLD (Delphi's path → Open House) ----------

:: TheKind.Session3.P3_World

@if session.p3_card.reversed:
    The World, inverted. The dancer in the wreath — completion, integration, wholeness — hangs reversed. Not failure, not incompletion. *Fear* of completion. The last step not taken because taking it makes everything real.

    The front door rattles. From inside. The store reaching for the lock, wanting to open, and hesitating. The building version of a hand on a doorknob, not turning.
@else:
    The World. The final card of the Major Arcana. The dancer in the wreath, surrounded by the four fixed signs — lion, eagle, bull, angel. Completion. Integration. The end of a journey and the beginning of everything that comes after.

    The front door swings open. On its own. Not a crack — *wide.* The storm is still raging outside, but the rain doesn't come in. The threshold holds. The warm air inside and the wild air outside meet at the doorframe and neither crosses. The store is opening itself up. Literally.
@endif

"Position three. What you want for yourself."

Scout stares at the open door. At the storm beyond. At the dry threshold.

"She opened the door," he says. "She opened the *door.*"

@if session.p3_card.reversed:
