:: TheKind.Session3.P3_World_Heart
"The World is integration," you say. "You don't want to be separate anymore. Not the odd building on Main Street, not the inside joke Rewind tells about itself. You want to be the *heart* of it. Lola's feeds people. Frame of Mind fixes bikes. You — you fix the thing that doesn't have a name. The ache. The search. The not-knowing-what-you're-looking-for. And you want Rewind to know that."

The door stays open. Through it, the traffic light on the corner — the incomprehensible one, the one nobody can explain — blinks. Green. In the direction of the store. For the first time in anyone's memory, the light makes sense.

"Did you see that?" Scout. Pressing his face against the window. "The traffic light just — it pointed at us."

"She called in a favor," Delphi says. "With the traffic light."

"You can't call in a favor with a TRAFFIC LIGHT."

"Kind of," Mal says, from the back stacks. And everyone almost laughs, because it's true. Kind of.

