The turntable hums. The speakers crackle. A fragment of sound — not quite music, not quite voice. Something between. The store trying to find its own frequency, reaching for a note it's been holding in its foundations for years.

Scout moves to the turntable. Not touching it — just standing near it. Close enough that the store can feel him there. "I'll find it," he says. "Whatever you want played, I'll find it."

